lic density, we find that all constrains complementarily work\nto narrow down the allowed parameter regions, and, especially, exclude $m_{Z'}\n\\lesssim 3.5$ TeV. For the obtained allowed regions, we calculate the\nspin-independent cross section of the RHN DM with nucleons. We find that the\nresultant cross section well below the current experimental upper bounds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 17 Apr 2017 16:32:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 8 Nov 2017 16:27:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-06"}
