s rate AGB stars at a distance of ~1.5 Rstar,\nin particular for the stars R Dor and W Hya, poses a challenge if one wishes to\nexplain both the dust spectral features in the spectral energy distribution\n(SED), in interferometric data, and in polarized light signal. In particular,\nthe estimated grain temperature of Al2O3 is too high for the grains to retain\ntheir amorphous structure. We propose that large gas-phase (Al2O3)n-clusters\n(n>34) can be the potential agents of the broad 11 micron feature in the SED\nand in the interferometric data and we explain how these large clusters can be\nformed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2017 08:50:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 23 Apr 2017 20:31:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-12-13"}
