timation of autoantibody signatures defined by presence\nor absence of a grid of landmark proteins. We show the pre-processing creates\nmore clearly separated clusters and improves the accuracy of autoantibody\nsubset detection via hierarchical clustering. Finally, we demonstrate the\nutility of the proposed methods with GEA data from scleroderma patients.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 18 Apr 2017 05:02:15 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 4 Aug 2017 05:06:12 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-07"}
